BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Codex//Best Kept Secret 2026//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:BKS - The Casbah
X-WR-TIMEZONE:Europe/Amsterdam
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e0f0385cc9f404f2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T131500Z
DTEND:20260612T140000Z
SUMMARY:Croíthe
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Darkly romantic noise rock up-and-comers\n\nFontaines D.C.\, Th
 e Murder Capital\, Sprints\, Gurriers... and now\, Croíthe appear to be t
 he next to grab the baton. Great bands from Ireland seem sprout to the sur
 face just about every second these days: Croíthe bring that darkly romant
 ic\, prowling goth/shoegaze sensibility that will make fans of Bauhaus\, S
 isters Of Mercy and fellow Dublin-dwellers Just Mustard salivate.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-617ac55da398fb0d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T144500Z
DTEND:20260612T153000Z
SUMMARY:Pacifica
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Pure-hearted\, cheeky garage bangers\n\nA good riff\, a good ho
 ok and pure attitude: Buenos Aires garage-duo Pacifica are the definition 
 of no-frills cool.\nIndeed\, the winds definitely worked in Inés Adam and
  Martina Nintzel’s favour when a random internet commenter – and a mut
 ual appreciation for The Strokes – brought them together to form a band.
  The duo’s combined brilliance forges earworms that illustrate the messi
 er aspects of being young\, in love with life and coping with all the trea
 cherous growing pains that come with that. Pacifica are fun\, frantic and 
 utterly in-your-face.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e7272a2b595f584c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T161500Z
DTEND:20260612T170000Z
SUMMARY:Elmer
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Non-conformist fusion of Dutch rap and theatre\n\nUnder her rap
 per alter ego Elmer\, Dutch artist & producer Merel Pauw is a bona fide in
 terloper\, causing shockwaves within the discourse of theatre\, hip-hop an
 d pop.On debut album ‘platland’\, Elmer forges a vital and off-beat mi
 x of rap\, techno and cabaret: a musical journey swerving between playful 
 agitation and deep reflection. Elmer’s shows celebrate the weird and pul
 l against the threads of gender roles and normative thinking with inventiv
 e (musical) contrasts and witty lyricism. A true cultural tour-de-force.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-bb8a8d904238a24e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T174500Z
DTEND:20260612T183000Z
SUMMARY:Shady Nasty
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Fiery mix of hip-hop\, post-punk and electronics\n\nAdd a Fred 
 again.. to your list of fans\, and things suddenly travel at warp-speed. T
 his is exactly what happened to Australian act Shady Nasty.Frankly\, the e
 nthusiasm is entirely justified\, because Shady Nasty's sound is as immedi
 ately bewitching as its tricky to define. Their adventurous productions sl
 ither in that liminal space between post-punk and hip-hop\, with lyrics ca
 ndidly channeling the everyday grind. Shady Nasty is already a cross-cultu
 ral marvel to truly reckon with.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-37ec14d503e30f6a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T191500Z
DTEND:20260612T200000Z
SUMMARY:Militarie Gun
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Post-hardcore of poetic honesty\n\nMilitarie Gun convert hard l
 uck tales into rousing\, satisfying releases like few other bands can.Foun
 ded by frontman Ian Shelton\, these American post-hardcore innovators rest
 lessly seek out small blades of hope and vulnerability peering out from th
 e hard-paved realities. They show that revolt isn’t just about shouting 
 at the masses: illustrating one’s daily concerns and struggles can strik
 e just as urgently.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-afe71c5d0a782fc5@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T204500Z
DTEND:20260612T213000Z
SUMMARY:Swordes
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Underground electro/hyperpop nonconformist\n\nCutting her teeth
  within the Brooklyn warehouse rave scenes\, Swordes makes - in her own wo
 rds - human music for humans.\nThe result is a headstrong hardware-only ap
 proach to composing\, producing and performing\, juxtaposing cutesy hyper 
 pop elements with gloomier\, gnarlier 80s electronica influences. Bubblegu
 m\, rainbows\, fire and gasoline: Swordes brings a club-friendly pop exorc
 ism that pierces like the sharpest of blades.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-95ef009df2e6ff6c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T221500Z
DTEND:20260612T230000Z
SUMMARY:supermodel*
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Catchy & distinctive genre-blender with DIY-ethos\n\nUS artist 
 Frankie Beanie's ground rules for his solo-project supermodel*: don't try 
 and be cool\, nick everything\, keep it lowercase\, don't overthink\, alwa
 ys talk about fight club. It translates to fun\, thrifty songs that channe
 l MF Doom as much as LCD Soundsystem. Beanie’s frank\, observational lyr
 ics draw partly from his experiences as an American living in the UK\, com
 plete with Be Kind Rewind-esque homages to Jamiroquai and Fatboy Slim. Eff
 ortlessly charming\, unpolished and yeah\, actually pretty damn cool.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-c187c140a24ff776@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T230000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Tramhaus (DJ Set)
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Casbah DJ set by Rotterdam's rowdiest band\n\nTramhaus's snowba
 lling success from Rotterdam's lively underground to one of Europe's great
 est livebands has been downright inspiring.\nAnd in that journey\, its mem
 bers have amassed a great deal of inspiration themselves from music both l
 ocal and far across the world. A breadth of influences and favorites disti
 lled down to an energetic DJ set at their familiar stomping grounds The Ca
 sbah.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5407dbcd93a6f8a6@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T101500Z
DTEND:20260613T110000Z
SUMMARY:Bruno Berle
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Supple polaroid filter latin pop\n\nThis Brazilian composer and
  troubadour writes honeysweet latin pop brimming with deft arrangements.\n
 From accounts of people who have been to Brazil\, it does seem like time w
 orks differently over there. Bruno Berle’s warm-blooded pop affirms this
  notion all the more. Carefree\, soft around the edges and unhurried\, Ber
 le’s tunes embrace you with the kind of affinity of a home-cooked meal. 
 For you lovers out there\, Bruno’s set at Best Kept would be good time t
 o get cosy.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-0c42b865f7818a2e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T114500Z
DTEND:20260613T123000Z
SUMMARY:Any Young Mechanic
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Jangly indie pop sensation\n\nAfter breaking out with their sun
 -kissed open-the-drapes single 'Snug Barber'\, this Aussie five-piece is i
 mmediately irresistable.\nMaintaining a fine-tuned balance between jangly 
 and cinematic\, Any Young Mechanic recall Vampire Weekend or perhaps a sli
 ghtly more mellowed out Violent Femmes. They embody the comfort of a fraye
 d sweater\, with an affable\, somewhat neurotic charm.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f89c6137b3654ae7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T131500Z
DTEND:20260613T140000Z
SUMMARY:Grote Geelstaart
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Math-tastic prog-noise minions\n\nImagine Geordie Greep frontin
 g Talking Heads instead of David Byrne: that's just one wild take on the b
 affling madness of rising Dutch outfit Grote Geelstaart.\nIf music was som
 ehow a math equation unlocking the fifth dimension in space\, Grote Geelst
 aart are the kind of band to figure it out\, using odd time signatures\, r
 iffs that scream 'fuck you\, diatonic scale!'\, and a lot of sweating it o
 ut through three-piece suits. Grote Geelstaart's music will flop like fish
  out of water\, only to magically grow arms and legs on the spot: rock mus
 ic evolving in real time!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-66b6fc533b1046cc@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T144500Z
DTEND:20260613T153000Z
SUMMARY:Etta Marcus
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Layered and atmospheric indie pop\n\nLonging\, sadness\, grit\,
  and dark humour: there’s always a lot of emotions coexisting in Etta Ma
 rcus’s songs.\nThat puts the Brixton-based songsmith in a rare echelon o
 f songwriters\, namely touchstones like Fiona Apple\, Hope Sandoval\, Jeff
  Buckley and Lana del Rey (Marcus opened for the latter). She is adept at 
 bittersweet\, layered gems that reconcile the highest of highs with the lo
 west of lows.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-8ced5227cecf5838@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T161500Z
DTEND:20260613T170000Z
SUMMARY:Crows
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Influential post-punk heavy-hitters\n\nThe ragged souls of Crow
 s take flight at Best Kept Secret with a top shelf slab of heavy-melodic p
 ost-punk.\nThe UK band have basically been your favorite band's favorite b
 and\; IDLES' Joe Talbot is one person who has professed how influential th
 ey were to his own group. Often pegged as brooding romantics\, Crows gigs 
 regularly unfold in spiritual\, sweaty communions. Emotional moshpits are 
 often the best\, right?
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9364e88f2ef0ccb2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T174500Z
DTEND:20260613T183000Z
SUMMARY:Midrift
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Prodigal shoegaze power trio\n\nThe kids are not only embracing
  shoegaze – they are taking it to someplace new. Midrift pepper in a bit
  of emo and pop punk to make things interesting. The path of these phenoms
  is not like some of their forebears\, toiling away with raggedy house sho
 ws at first. Frontman Gus Mehrkam created his songs in his bedroom\, uploa
 ded them on TikTok\, and bang! They became viral hits. With skirmishing si
 blings Kai and Manoa Neukermans completing the power trio\, Midrift are ju
 stly what people call 'an overnight sensation'.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-3e054165291ef2d4@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T191500Z
DTEND:20260613T200000Z
SUMMARY:GHOSTWOMAN
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Dynamic transatlantic rock duo\n\nNo genre has been declared de
 ad more than rock\; yet the duo of GHOSTWOMAN fancies itself as fiery necr
 omancers\, reinventing its raw power all over again.Canadian Evan Uschenko
  (guitars/vocals) and Belgian Ille van Dessel (drums/percussion) began the
 ir voyage an entire ocean apart: now their collision course brings new tre
 mors in activity\, exploring rock of the psychedelic\, stoner\, garage and
  indie variety through the prism of their own infectious chemistry.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-bcca7406699dca92@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T204500Z
DTEND:20260613T213000Z
SUMMARY:Kumo 99
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Underground hardcore/breakbeat with need for speed\n\nWith big 
 beats and an even bigger attitude\, Kumo 99 put a fresh spin on the deligh
 tfully abrasive rave nostalgia of the 90s.The Los Angeles artist duo of Am
 i Komai and Nate Donmoyer don’t play it subtle when it comes to serving 
 up a clamouring bricolage of breakbeats\, industrial and digitised hardcor
 e. Kumo 99 have toured with artists as diverse as Magdalena Bay and The Ar
 med\, showing that their explosive club anthems will crush in virtually an
 y context.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-95333e67cfd50186@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T221500Z
DTEND:20260613T230000Z
SUMMARY:Dame Area
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Acidic & percussive industrial romps\n\nRemember that one Death
  Grips-lyric about having the DNA of gothic lemons? It describes Barcelona
  industrial duo Dame Area to a tee. Their sound is both abrasive and stran
 gely whimsical: hissy\, static-laden textures\, bile-drenched polyrhythms 
 and shouty vocals that sound like they've been recorded in claustrophobic 
 solitary confinement. Dame Area put a fresh and fun spin on industrial mus
 ic\, marrying 'rave' and 'ravenous' in novel\, eye-opening ways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a8746986e56f3480@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T230000Z
DTEND:20260614T000000Z
SUMMARY:MEROL (DJ Debut)
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Dutch pop's Most Entertaining Role Model\n\nA Casbah DJ set by 
 one of today’s most impactful Dutch artists.\nMEROL is dropping a brand 
 new album. 'Leve de Feeks' is punk\, a middle finger and above all a liber
 ation of the openly sexual\, outspoken woman. For her DJ debut she'll be s
 pinning the tracks that shaped her\, from riot grrrl punk to techno.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-784f2bcae397f410@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T000000Z
DTEND:20260614T020000Z
SUMMARY:Here's The Thing DJ Set
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Post-punk\, psych rock\, indie rock and all that goodness inbet
 ween\n\nThere's nothing quite like the squeak of an amp\, the rumble of a 
 bass\, the hiss of cymbals before things are about to get real.\nThese hea
 ds from the recurring Tilburg festival know their stuff when it comes to t
 he latest noise from the fringes. From weirdos in basements to firebrands 
 prowling the bigger stages\, the landscape of genre-pushing guitar-based m
 usic seems more diverse than ever before. Here's The Thing will bundle it 
 all into a supercharged spendour!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5ef3b97c1ebdc5b2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T100000Z
DTEND:20260614T104500Z
SUMMARY:Apichat Pakwan
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Balmy blend of Thai music & electronics\n\nApichat Pakwan bring
 s a lively crossover of electronics and Thai esan and molam movements: the
  sweetest balance between the modern and the traditional.It unfolds miracu
 lously live as well: you have producer Olivier Schreuder serving up beats 
 that blend seamlessly with the Thai musicians and singers: not in that cru
 de mash-up kind of way\, but warmly courting each other in a tryst. This a
 pproach carries over to audiences\, creating a hot & sweltering dancefloor
  environment.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fadb2e311adc2163@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T111500Z
DTEND:20260614T120000Z
SUMMARY:DYGL
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Japanese garage rock torch bearers\n\nJapanese garage rockers D
 YGL (pronounced 'day glo') embody pure exuberance and rebellion with their
  catchy-as-sin anthems.\nThat the four piece's swagger and songwriting acu
 men holds up against any of their forebears in evident in the fact that Th
 e Strokes' Albert Hammond Jr. decided to take it upon himself to produce D
 YGL's debut album. So who's in the house?Curated by Tramhaus
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-20b56f9610ab534b@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T123000Z
DTEND:20260614T131500Z
SUMMARY:Servo
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Brutal psych noise beast\n\nFrench trio Servo are a high mass o
 f pure uncompromising noise rock: dangerous\, devastating and no wasted mo
 vements.\nBrandishing locomotive rhythms\, noise hexes of the spine-chilli
 ng variety and demonic vocals\, Servo aren’t concerned with adding tons 
 of bells and whistles: their songs go straight for the jugular and send au
 diences right back to the stone ages. Hunting season is open this summer. 
 Curated by Tramhaus
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-c0f5af1d5946018a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T134500Z
DTEND:20260614T143000Z
SUMMARY:Good Flying Birds
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Lo-fi jangle pop up-and-comers\n\nGood Flying Birds are a young
  band who are happy being a throwback: capturing contagious powerpop gems 
 with lo-fi home recordings.\nIt’s no coincidence they are named after a 
 Guided By Voices-song\, a band emblematic of such a sprightly modus operan
 di. Delightfully chaotic\, hodgepodge and impulsive\, the chaos Good Flyin
 g Birds sow with a bunch of instruments in the room seems to inevitably ma
 nifest into tunes you’ll hum along for days on end.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cbf3f2752b0e69d1@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T151500Z
DTEND:20260614T160000Z
SUMMARY:Another Country $$$$
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Genre-fluid experimental rock enigma\n\nManchester experimental
  outfit Another Country $$$$ has no qualms jumping into the deep end: whol
 ly unconcerned with genre tropes\, eternally fluid and free.\nExperimental
  rock\, IDM\, ambient pop\, mathcore: defining Another Country $$$$ is dep
 endent on who you ask. The group’s creativity isn’t based on fixed out
 comes\, but constant metamorphosis. Chalk it up to a constant remix\, comp
 ulsively courting uncharted sonic expressways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f42449cbad9a92a5@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T164500Z
DTEND:20260614T173000Z
SUMMARY:C'est Qui?
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Politically-charged\, powder keg punk anthems\n\nC’est Qui? w
 on’t settle for compromise within their witty\, politically-charged punk
  tunes.Anger is just the tip of the iceberg for this plucky young outfit: 
 sadness\, frustration\, despair\, resilience and joy\; these are the very 
 roots from which their scuzzy\, outspoken anthems sprout. C’est Qui? suc
 k out the poison from society’s festering wounds with pure exuberance an
 d explosiveness.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5418ceccd654e54b@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T181500Z
DTEND:20260614T190000Z
SUMMARY:Lime Garden
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Hook-heavy & heartfelt indie pop\n\nLime Garden’s irresistibl
 e blend of post-punk\, synth pop\, and indie rock marries romance with the
  mundane.On sophomore album Maybe Not Tonight\, the Brighton band illustra
 te the fickle dynamics of nightlife – where starry-eyed expectations and
  frantic fun can promptly spiral into melancholy and chaos. Beneath an end
 less array of cheeky hooks\, sizzling melodies and plunging rhythms\, Lime
  Garden’s brilliance rests on a fundamental force: their friendship.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fd7c3648764cbfa6@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T200000Z
DTEND:20260614T220000Z
SUMMARY:WK Nederland - Japan
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:The World Cup match Netherlands – Japan will be broadcast at 
 The Casbah\, presented by Kartje Kilo!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-98b917fdf96df32e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T131500Z
DTEND:20260611T140000Z
